comments: Markkanen (UTA) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Durant's (PHX) arm.
Collins (UTA) firms up over his right foot in Booker's (PHX) path and marginal leg to leg contact occurs as Booker defends over the pick.
Clarkson (UTA) overtly extends his leg to create the marginal contact with Booker (PHX) during the jump shot attempt.
George (UTA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Allen (PHX) during the steal.
Booker (PHX) rests his hand on George's (UTA) front and marginal body contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Durant (PHX) firms up in George's (UTA) path over his right foot and does not deliver illegal contact.
Collins (UTA) jumps A to B into the body of Durant (PHX), affecting his trajectory during the dunk attempt.
Collins (UTA) establishes himself in Allen's (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.

Replay review of the foul called on Booker (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  Booker (PHX) initiates contact across Collins' (UTA) arm that affects his ability to secure the rebound.  Although Markkanen (UTA) is at the free throw line prior to the timeout and challenge, replay review confirms that Booker fouls Collins, who is awarded the free throws when play resumes.
Agbaji (UTA) legally contests Durant's (PHX) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Bates-Diop (PHX) cleanly blocks Markkanen's (UTA) driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) has both hands on the ball and any ensuing contact with Markkanen (UTA) is incidental.
Collins (UTA) commits a take foul on Allen (PHX).
Durant (PHX) is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Allen (PHX) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Clarkson's (UTA) head.
Allen (PHX) releases the throw-in within five seconds.
